'''2016年－2017年冈比亚憲政危機'''始於2016年12月1日[[2016年岡比亞總統選舉|總統選舉]]，該次選舉由[[阿達馬·巴羅|阿達馬·巴羅]]勝出，長期執政的時任總統[[叶海亚·贾梅|叶海亚·贾梅]]起初接受自己敗選的選舉結果，但8日後贾梅拒絕接受選舉結果。冈比亚軍隊隨後集結於[[班竹|班竹]]及[[萨拉昆达|萨拉昆达]]。國內及國際上對贾梅的決定表示不滿，[[西非国家经济共同体|西非国家经济共同体]]則派遣代表團試圖說服贾梅接受選舉結果。

== 国际干预 ==
[[西非国家经济共同体|西非国家经济共同体]]表示將會承認巴羅為岡比亞新一屆總統，並在[[塞内加尔|塞内加尔]]與冈比亚的边界上集結軍隊為介入作準備。2017年1月18日，冈比亚军方首脑巴德杰表示如果其它国家的军队越过边界，他的部队不準備抵抗。<ref name=voa20170119>{{Cite_news |url=http://www.voachinese.com/a/gambia-20170119/3682639.html |title=冈比亚落选总统拒下台 非洲国家忙斡旋 |publisher=美國之音 |date=2017-01-19 |accessdate=2017-01-19 |archive-date=2017-01-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120130052/http://www.voachinese.com/a/gambia-20170119/3682639.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>巴罗于19日在位于塞内加尔首都[[达喀尔|达喀尔]]的-{zh-cn:冈比亚;zh-hk:甘比亞}-大使馆宣誓就职，西非国家联合军队同日自两国边境进入冈比亚。<ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/gambia-president-elect-plans-inauguration-senegal-44879387|title=Regional Troops Enter Gambia in Effort to Get Jammeh to Go|publisher=ABC News|date=2017-01-19|accessdate=2017-01-20|archive-date=2017-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120022304/http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/gambia-president-elect-plans-inauguration-senegal-44879387|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-38682184|title=Gambia crisis: Senegal sends in troops to back elected leader|date=2017-01-19|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2017-01-20|archive-date=2017-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120084353/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-38682184|dead-url=no}}</ref>贾梅向西非国家经济共同体提出条件，要求赦免其在任职总统时犯下的罪行，并允许其留在冈比亚境内，但遭到该组织拒绝。巴德杰于20日宣誓效忠新总统巴罗。贾梅于21日清晨发表声明同意下台，随后搭機离开甘比亞，輾轉逃亡到[[赤道几内亚|赤道几内亚]]。<ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/01/gambia-yahya-jammeh-agrees-step-170120184330091.html|title=Gambia's Yahya Jammeh confirms he will step down|publisher=Aljazeera|date=2017-01-21|accessdate=2017-01-21|archive-date=2020-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200829203126/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/01/gambia-yahya-jammeh-agrees-step-170120184330091.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite_news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/20/yahya-jammeh-given-high-noon-deadline-relinquish-power-gambia/|title=Gambia's Yahya Jammeh agrees to step down peacefully and red carpet is rolled out at the airport, amid last-ditch negotiations|publisher=Telegraph|date=2017-01-21|accessdate=2017-01-21|archive-date=2017-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170121040043/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/20/yahya-jammeh-given-high-noon-deadline-relinquish-power-gambia/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-gambia-politics-idUSKBN15505N|title=Gambia's former leader Jammeh flies into exile: mediators|publisher=Reuters|date=2017-01-21|accessdate=2017-01-22|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122003830/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-gambia-politics-idUSKBN15505N|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/01/20/africa/gambia-janmeh-barrow-ecowas/|title=Gambia: Defeated leader Jammeh leaves country after election loss|publisher=CNN|date=2017-01-22|accessdate=2017-01-21|archive-date=2017-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120201239/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/01/20/africa/gambia-janmeh-barrow-ecowas/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

